Sample Questions for the Deep Research Agent
=============================================

SINGLE-DATASET QUESTIONS
--------------------------
1. Which countries have the highest GDP per capita but also the highest CO2 emissions per capita?
2. What is the trend in global temperature anomalies between 1990 and 2023?
3. Which diseases have the highest treatment gaps and lowest vaccine coverage?
4. Which cities have the worst air quality index despite being in high-income countries?
5. What share of scientific publications in AI come from China vs. the US, and how has that changed since 2018?

CROSS-DATASET / ANALYTICAL QUESTIONS
--------------------------------------
6. Is there a correlation between a country's internet penetration rate and its unemployment rate?
7. Do countries with higher public education spending tend to score better on PISA math tests?
8. Which regions are seeing both population growth and rising CO2 emissions simultaneously?
9. Compare renewable energy capacity share against CO2 emissions per capita -- are high-renewable countries actually lower emitters?
10. Is there a relationship between a country's Global Peace Index score and its food security index?

TREND & FORECASTING QUESTIONS
-------------------------------
11. Based on the CO2 emissions trend from 2018-2023, which countries are on track to reduce emissions and which are not?
12. How has the share of open-access scientific publications changed across all research fields since 2018?
13. Which biomes have experienced the largest biodiversity loss relative to habitat loss since 2000?

SYNTHESIS / POLICY QUESTIONS
------------------------------
14. Which countries have high AI readiness but low internet penetration -- where is the digital divide largest among AI-capable nations?
15. What common factors do the top 5 most food-secure countries share in terms of GDP, education, and trade balance?
16. Given mental health prevalence rates, suicide rates, and psychiatrist availability, which countries have the most underserved mental health populations?
17. Which megacities combine high population density, poor air quality, and low public transit coverage -- and what does that suggest about infrastructure investment needs?

MULTI-HOP REASONING QUESTIONS (hardest)
-----------------------------------------
18. Countries with high fertility rates tend to have younger median ages -- does that correlate with higher or lower AI adoption readiness in this dataset?
19. Identify countries that rank in the bottom third for food security AND have experienced more than 20% habitat loss since 1970 in their primary biome.
20. Which countries are simultaneously increasing renewable energy capacity, reducing CO2 emissions, and maintaining GDP growth above 2%?
